  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The primary aim of the study is to assess whether 6-months of vitamin D supplements can
      decrease PTH compared with placebo treatment in primary hyperparathyroidism.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The study investigates effects and safety of six months of vitamin D supplementation before
      and after surgery in primary hyperparathyroidism. Effects are assessed as changes in calcium
      homeostasis, bone metabolism, quality of life, and muscle strength and function.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
